# Koolu

<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/hendry/1790045443/" title="Photo Sharing"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2375/1790045443_80e5e8e2c8_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Trying to install Debian on a Koolu" /></a>

Koolu is a [AMD Geode](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AMD_Geode) based ["mini
PC"](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Linux_mini_computers). The same
processor used in the [Linutop](http://www.linutop.com/).

# Pros

* Silent
* Small physical footprint
* Robust
* Low energy consumption

# Cons

* Long order times
* `acpi=off` to boot succesfully
* Needs some patches with the video drivers
* No [[networking]]
* You need to arrange monitor, keyboard and mouse
* [Sluggish CPU](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amd_geode#AMD_Geode)




